OBINNA EZUGWU The Federal Ministry of Education has announced that secondary school for exit classes will resume on August 4, 2020. The ministry which announced this in a statement signed by its Director Press and Public Relation, Ben Goong on Monday, said students will have two weeks to prepare for the West African Examination, WAEC which will start on the 17th of August. “Secondary schools in the country are to reopen as from the 4th of August, 2020 for exit classes only,” the statement said.